le drone on shelves.  </p>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">When I walked into my local Best Buy store today, June 24th, there were zero DJI drones available to purchase. There wasn't even an empty spot for each drone to go. The entire DJI aisle had been swept clean of price tags, lockers, and products - save a handful of motorized gimbals, action cameras, a single lone RC controller, and an almost empty premium endcap spot where a flagship drone would normally go. </p>\n<img src=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/06/dji-best-buy-aisle-sean-hollister.jpg?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0,10.732984293194,100,78.534031413613\" alt=\"Empty shelves, missing price tags and lockers in the DJI section of Best Buy.\" title=\"Empty shelves, missing price tags and lockers in the DJI section of Best Buy.\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" data-caption=\"&lt;em&gt;Here is the DJI section at my local Best Buy.&lt;/em&gt; | Photo by Sean Hollister / The Verge\" data-portal-copyright=\"Photo by Sean Hollister / The Verge\"><img src=\"https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/06/immersive-flight-experience-best-buy-dji.jpg?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0,13.387397942372,100,73.225204115256\" alt=\"A case with an empty spot where drones used to go.\" title=\"A case with an empty spot where drones used to go.\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" data-portal-copyright=\"Photo by Sean Hollister / The Verge\">\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">\"We're not really carrying DJI drones anymore because of the US-China thing,\" a store employee told me. </p>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Best Buy is not alone. DJI's own US webstore no longer has <em>any </em>drones in stock, <a href=\"https://dronedj.com/2025/06/23/every-dji-drone-is-out-of-stock-on-the-companys-online-store/\">as <em>DroneDJ </em>reported</a> Monday. Despite DJI having an official presence on Amazon, all remaining drones there are sold by third parties with low or u